abstract: A reality TV series about the A.S.P.C.A. police unit that rescues animals from abuse overstates its effectiveness, critics say.
snippet: A reality TV series about the A.S.P.C.A. police unit that rescues animals from abuse overstates its effectiveness, critics say.
lead_paragraph: “Animal Precinct,” the six-year-old reality TV series, has long been more than just a gritty chronicle of the A.S.P.C.A. police unit that specializes in rescuing animals victimized by cruelty in New York City.

abstract:
The most radical congressman in America is a Republican
from Texas. And he’s running for president.
snippet:
The most radical congressman in America is a Republican
from Texas. And he’s running for president.
lead_paragraph: Whipping westward across Manhattan in a limousine sent by Comedy Central’s “Daily Show,” Ron Paul, the 10-term Texas congressman and long-shot Republican presidential candidate, is being briefed. Paul has only the most tenuous familiarity with Comedy Central. He has never heard of “The Daily Show.” His press secretary, Jesse Benton, is trying to explain who its host, Jon Stewart, is. “He’s an affable gentleman,” Benton says, “and he’s very smart. What I’m getting from the pre-interview is, he’s sympathetic.”
